                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/731.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s July 23. Department of Hacienda informed me this afternoon that
                    tomorrow recommendation will be made by telegraph permitting the old tax to be
                    effective for the present quarter only, “not because the new rate is unjust but
                    as a temporary concession in view of the circumstances related by the Consul
                    General.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
